Adamawa State Governor, Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri, has presented a staff of office to the new Chief of Lunguda Kingdom, Mr Kurhaye Dishon Dansansa. Dansanda was on Saturday turbaned as the 17th Kwandi Nungurya of Guyuk chiefdom. Fintiri congratulated the king makers and the people of Lunguda for the show of maturity and understanding displayed during the selection of the new Kwandi Nungurya to fill the vacuum created by the demise of the late Alfred Kimde. He commended the spirit of oneness and togetherness that guided the conduct of the exercise which proved that the admirable Lunguda culture is intact and will continue prevail and also confirmed that the new Chief commands a lot of respect and support from his subjects. He called on the royal father to reciprocate the gesture of the people through providing exemplary leadership that places emphasis on the promotion of ethnic, social and religious harmony among the people at all times. The governor urged traditional rulers in the state as custodians of culture to play more dynamic and prominent role in mobilizing the people at the grassroots towards engaging in meaningful economic ventures and self help projects which will uplift the living standard of the people. He implored people of the state to avoid idleness which leads to anti social and criminal activities ranging from kidnapping, armed banditry, cattle rustling, famers-herders clashes and insurgency urging them to cooperate with the royal fathers and government for peace in the state.